This along with the visual chart is to demonstrate how the information moves, why it moves and what it supports.
Which engines feed into which Dashboard.

Engines > Dashboards
Data Collection Engine >  None (backend service)
Data Processing Engine >  None (backend service)
Compliance Engine	     >    Compliance Dashboard, Executive Dashboard
Vulnerability Correlation Engine	>  Vulnerability Dashboard, Risk Dashboard, Executive Dashboard
Asset Management Engine  >	Asset Dashboard, Executive Dashboard
Risk Assessment Engine	>  Risk Dashboard, Executive Dashboard
POA&M Management Engine	>  POA&M Dashboard, Executive Dashboard


Dashboard Dependencies

##Executive Dashboard

The executive dashboard should consume nearly everything.

Compliance Engine
Risk Assessment Engine
Vulnerability Correlation Engine
Asset Management Engine
POA&M Management Engine

Metrics to include:

Overall Compliance
Overall Risk Score
Patch Compliance
Critical Findings
Open POA&Ms
Asset Health
Monthly Trends


##Compliance Dashboard

Consumes only the Compliance Engine.

Shows:

Control Family Scores
Failed Controls
Framework Compliance
Evidence Coverage
Audit Readiness


##Vulnerability Dashboard

Consumes the Vulnerability Correlation Engine.

Shows:

Critical/High/Medium/Low
CVE Trends
CVSS Distribution
Duplicate Findings Removed
Scanner Comparison
Top Vulnerabilities


##Asset Dashboard

Consumes the Asset Management Engine.

Shows:

Server Count
Workstation Count
Switches
Firewalls
Unsupported Systems
Patch Status
Backup Status
Offline Assets


##Risk Dashboard

Consumes:
Risk Assessment Engine
Vulnerability Correlation Engine

Shows:

Risk Heat Map
Risk Register
Likelihood vs Impact
Top Business Risks
Trending Risk Score
High-Risk Assets


##POA&M Dashboard

Consumes: 
POA&M Management Engine
Risk Assessment Engine
Compliance Engine

Shows:

Open POA&Ms
Closed POA&Ms
Overdue Items
Upcoming Milestones
Responsible Owners
SLA Compliance
